  I(10) mod 10 = 1 always (trivially, since 10|10*a1 and 10|100*a2)
  I(11) mod 11 = (1 + a1 + a2) mod 11 (since 11*a1 = 0 mod 11, 121*a2 = 0 mod 11)

  I(11) mod 11 = 1 always (since 11 | 11*a1 and 11 | 121*a2)
  In fact: I(b) mod b = 1 for ALL b (since b | b*a1 and b | b^2*a2)
  This is just I(Omega, 0) = 1 mod b.

